om\": 385, \"to\": 400}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butker, who is outspoken in his defense of the Traditional Latin Mass (TLM) and Christianity in general, quoted a Bible verse in response to the grotesque display.\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 566, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Butker\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 409}, {\"ngram\": \"his defense\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 442}, {\"ngram\": \"the Traditional Latin Mass\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 472}, {\"ngram\": \"TLM\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 477}, {\"ngram\": \"a Bible verse\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 528}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 540}, {\"ngram\": \"the grotesque display\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 565}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The parody also drew a sharp rebuke from French bishops who wrote, \\\"Christians on all continents who have been hurt by the outrageousness and provocation\\\" of the event, the bishopssaidthey deeply deplored the \\\"scenes of derision and mockery of Christianity\\\" American Bishop Robert Barron alsodecriedthe display, calling it a \\\"gross mockery of Christianity,\\\" \\\"France felt evidently that as it's trying to put its best cultural foot forward the right thing to do is to mock this very central moment in Christianity where Jesus at his Last Supper gives his body and blood in anticipation of the cross,\\\" Barron said in avideoposted on X (former Twitter).\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.66113709107465, \"rank\": 0.5121321570558206, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.6586291498446323, \"rank\": 0.43553352206221796, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"db